+++ b/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,61 @@
+# logpipe
+
+A CLI log-analysis tool. Point it at one or more log files in different
+formats — JSON-lines, syslog, Apache/nginx CLF, or your own regex-described
+format — and it normalizes everything into a common event model, runs
+configurable filters/transforms, computes windowed metrics, flags anomalous
+spikes/drops, and produces both a JSON report and a readable summary.
+
+Stdlib + PyYAML only.
+
+## Install
+
+```bash
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+## Commands
+
+```bash
+# Batch analysis — text summary to stdout, JSON report to file
+logpipe analyze app.jsonl /var/log/syslog access.log -c logpipe.yaml -o report.json
+
+# Same but print JSON to stdout
+logpipe analyze app.jsonl -f json
+
+# Real-time monitoring with rolling analysis (Ctrl-C for final summary)
+logpipe tail /var/log/syslog app.jsonl -c logpipe.yaml --refresh 10
+
+# Just show what format each file is detected as
+logpipe detect *.log
+```
+
+## Config file
+
+All sections optional. See `examples/logpipe.yaml`.
+
+```yaml
+parsers:
+  custom:
+    - name: myapp
+      pattern: '^(?P<timestamp>\S+) \[(?P<level>\w+)\] (?P<message>.*)$'
+      time_format: '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S'
+
+filters:
+  - { type: level,   min: WARNING }
+  - { type: exclude, field: message, pattern: 'healthcheck' }
+
+transforms:
+  - { type: set, field: env, value: prod }
+
+analysis:
+  window_seconds: 60
+  anomaly_z: 2.5
+  top_messages: 10
+```
+
+## Resilience
+
+* Unreadable files are warned about and skipped — they never abort the run.
+* Malformed lines are counted, warned, and skipped.
+* Unknown filter/transform/parser types in config are warned and ignored.
